2026-07-18T04:42:43.0336983Z >>> grub2-probe: error: failed to get canonical path of `overlay'.
2026-07-18T04:42:43.2383136Z 2026-07-18 04:42:43,237: livemedia-creator v44.6-1
2026-07-18T04:42:43.2383771Z 2026-07-18 04:42:43,237: selinux is Disabled
2026-07-18T04:42:43.2388896Z 2026-07-18 04:42:43,238: The disk image /workspace/live-disk-result/azurelinux-desktop-live.img is missing.
2026-07-18T04:42:44.0258924Z ##[error]Process completed with exit code 1.

Root cause: --disk-image points livemedia-creator at an already-existing
disk image to reinstall onto. It is not an output path for --make-disk
to create fresh. lorax's own argument validation (src/pylorax/cmdline/
livemedia.py) checks `if opts.disk_image and not os.path.exists(opts.
disk_image): errors.append("The disk image %s is missing." % opts.
disk_image)` unconditionally, before any real work starts. --image-size
also isn't a real flag at all - only --image-size-align exists, and
argparse's prefix matching silently treated the "--image-size 24" we
passed as an abbreviation of that unrelated flag, so it was never doing
what it looked like it was doing either way.

Fix: drop --disk-image and --image-size, use --image-name <filename>
instead (joined with --resultdir for the actual output path). Size gets
calculated automatically from the kickstart's own partition sizes
(src/pylorax/creator.py, calculate_disk_size()) - there is no manual
size flag for a from-scratch --make-disk build.

The grub2-probe error one line above the livemedia-creator banner is
unrelated noise from the toolchain-install container (dnf5 installing
lorax itself), not from the actual livemedia-creator run.
